
# Data & Business Analyst | MSc Supply Chain Analytics | Ex–Transaction Banking Sales

Welcome to my e-portfolio! I am currently pursuing a Master’s in Supply Chain Analytics, building advanced skills in data analysis, forecasting, and business intelligence. With prior experience in transaction banking sales, I bring a strong understanding of financial services, client management, and commercial strategy. I am now focused on applying analytical tools such as Python, SQL, and Power BI to solve business and operational challenges. My work includes projects in transportation cost analysis, forecasting, and supply chain optimization—turning data into actionable insights.

I am interested in roles in business analytics, supply chain, and financial services where I can combine data, strategy, and real-world impact.

## 📌 Objective

To obtain a challenging analyst role where I can contribute to impactful projects, learn from experienced professionals, and continue improving my data analysis and problem-solving skills.

### 💼 Work Experience

### **TRANSACTION BANKING SALES (CORPORATE)** - *PermataBank Jakarta (part of Bangkok Bank Group)*
*July 2021 - July 2025*

• Managed a portfolio of 100+ corporate clients across FMCG, Telecommunications, and Auto Parts industries as sole point of contact for all inquiries, escalations, and strategic initiatives, achieving a 90%+ client retention rate throughout tenure.

• Onboarded 50+ new clients to Trade Finance and Cash Management solutions — including Letters of Credit, Bank Guarantees, and Standby LCs — by conducting tailored product walkthroughs and structuring deal terms aligned to each client's working capital cycle, reducing average onboarding time by 20%.

• Grew Trade Finance transaction volume 30%+ year-over-year by developing customized client business plans, identifying upsell opportunities across Core, Risk, and Liquidity product lines, and executing end-to-end deal structuring with internal credit and risk teams.

• Accelerated deal closure timelines by 25% by coordinating across AML, compliance, finance, and product units, ensuring timely and accurate responses to client requests and regulatory requirements on all Trade Finance and Cash Management facilities.

• Improved client portfolio profitability by analyzing payment portfolio metrics and cash flow data across 100+ accounts, delivering monthly performance reviews to senior management and recommending adjustments to fee structures, credit limits, and product mix.

• Ensured regulatory adherence across all client engagements by collaborating with AML and credit risk units to assess financial exposure, supporting full compliance with banking regulations and internal risk frameworks.

### **SUPPLY CHAIN ANALYST** - *Onboard XP, LLC*
*November 2018 - July 2021* 

• Managed procurement and product development engagements for 40+ airline clients by leading end-to-end RFP reviews, structuring competitive pricing proposals, and collaborating with internal product teams, contributing to an 85% contract renewal rate.

• Reduced average bid response time by 30% by standardizing the RFP evaluation and pricing framework, enabling faster, more consistent proposal delivery across airline stakeholders and vendor negotiations.

• Oversaw shipment coordination for airline supply orders across 10+ routes by tracking real-time logistics performance via ERP systems and resolving transit disruptions within 24 hours, achieving a 98% on-time delivery rate for critical aviation components.

• Improved inventory accuracy by 20% by building demand forecasting models in Excel, analyzing historical sales trends and seasonal demand patterns across airline accounts to ensure optimal stock positioning.

